# =============================================================================
# TrAIding Floor — environment variables (template)
# =============================================================================
# Copy this file to user-data/.env, then either edit by hand OR — much
# easier — leave it empty and let the onboarding wizard fill it in for
# you on first launch (http://localhost/onboarding/welcome).
#
#   mkdir -p user-data
#   cp .env.example user-data/.env
#
# Everything below is OPTIONAL. The required exchange/wallet entries are
# written by the wizard.
# =============================================================================


# ── OPTIONAL: Anthropic (LLM reviewer + agent chat) ──────────────────────────
# Without this key, the head trader runs in deterministic-only mode (rules
# + library + beliefs). With it, the LLM reviewer auto-attaches and reviews
# every proposed action. Default authority is "deterministic_wins" so rules
# still win until you flip the knob from the dashboard.
# Get a key at https://console.anthropic.com
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...


# ── OPTIONAL: OpenAI (alternative LLM brain) ─────────────────────────────────
# Pick one OR the other — you don't need both. OpenAI is configurable in the
# onboarding wizard's "Brain" step.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...


# ── OPTIONAL: Ollama (fully local LLM brain) ─────────────────────────────────
# Free, runs on your machine, no API key. Requires Ollama running on the
# host. The wizard's "Brain" step picks this up automatically when you
# select it.
# OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://host.docker.internal:11434


# ── OPTIONAL: Telegram alert watcher ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Uncomment the traiding-watcher service in docker-compose.yml AND set
# both of these to get alerts on drawdown, agent dead, circuit broken, etc.
# Create a bot via @BotFather on Telegram; get the chat ID via @userinfobot.
# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=
# TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=


# ── OPTIONAL: Dune Analytics intel ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Enables a sidecar that polls Dune Analytics for cross-venue funding arb
# signals, alt-coin funding maps, and whale leaderboards every 10 minutes.
# The head trader's LLM brain auto-uses this as context.
# Get a key at https://dune.com/settings/api (free tier is enough).
# DUNE_API_KEY=


# ── Venue selection ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Default is hyperliquid. Other supported values:
#   hyperliquid, binance, okx, kucoin, bybit, mock, paper
# The wizard sets this automatically when you pick an exchange.
# TF_VENUE=hyperliquid


# ── Cross-venue arb ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Comma-separated list of venues for cross-venue funding arb. Each venue
# needs its own credentials (set via the wizard's per-venue keys step).
# Example: TF_CROSS_VENUES=hyperliquid,binance,okx
# TF_CROSS_VENUES=
